  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_care_programme_approach">Care Programme Approach</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_care_programme_approach">CPA</xref>) provides a framework for effective mental health care planning, assessment, management, co-ordination and delivery.        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_care_programme_approach">Care Programme Approach</xref>
 only applies to individuals with complex needs who are in contact with a number of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICES</xref>, or those at most risk.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on the 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_care_programme_approach">Care Programme Approach</xref>, see the NHS website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/social-care-and-support-guide/help-from-social-services-and-charities/care-for-people-with-mental-health-problems-care-programme-approach/"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Care Programme Approach</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
